OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1779343523
OL,3,CConsumer confidence rises slightly
OL,4,Cfollowing signs of Iran 'de-escalation'
OL,6,FConsumer confidence saw a slight
OL,7,Fimprovement this month following signs
OL,8,Fof de-escalation in the Middle East,
OL,9,Ffigures suggest.
OL,11,FConfidence in the economy over the
OL,12,Fnext three months remains firmly in
OL,13,Fnegative territory at minus 48, but up
OL,14,Ffrom minus 53 last month, according to
OL,15,FBritish Retail Consortium (BRC) and
OL,16,FOpinium data.
OL,18,FConfidence in personal finances also
OL,19,Frose slightly from minus 21 in April
OL,20,Fto minus 16.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/5
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1779343523
OL,3,CConsumer confidence rises slightly
OL,4,Cfollowing signs of Iran 'de-escalation'
OL,6,FHowever, the proportion of people
OL,7,Fconcerned that conflict in the Middle
OL,8,FEast could increase food prices rose
OL,9,Fto 82% in May, up from 80% last month,
OL,10,Fwhile 83% are now concerned about the
OL,11,Fcrisis leading to higher energy bills,
OL,12,Fup from 81%.
OL,14,FThe survey was taken ahead of latest
OL,15,Fpredictions that Ofgem's next price
OL,16,Fcap will rise by #209 a year from July
OL,17,Famid the fallout of the Iran war, with
OL,18,Fexperts warning over an impending
OL,19,Fpayment shock from the autumn as
OL,20,Fdemand surges in the cooler months.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/5
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1779343523
OL,3,CConsumer confidence rises slightly
OL,4,Cfollowing signs of Iran 'de-escalation'
OL,6,FCornwall Insight said its prediction
OL,7,Ffor Ofgem's cap from July to September
OL,8,Fnow stands at #1,850 for a typical
OL,9,Fdual fuel household, an increase of
OL,10,F13% on April's #1,641 annual cap.
OL,12,FThis is slightly higher than the 12%
OL,13,Fincrease it forecast last month.
OL,15,FBRC chief executive Helen Dickinson
OL,16,Fsaid: "Consumer confidence, while
OL,17,Ffirmly negative, saw a slight lift in
OL,18,FMay following signs of de-escalation
OL,19,Fin the Middle East.
OL,26,@xD@GOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/5
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
