OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1779343523
OL,3,CConsumer confidence rises slightly
OL,4,Cfollowing signs of Iran 'de-escalation'
OL,6,F"Younger consumers drove this
OL,7,Fimprovement in expectations for the
OL,8,Feconomy and household finances, helped
OL,9,Fby rising real wages among this
OL,10,Fgeneration.
OL,12,F"But the outlook remains fragile:
OL,13,Finflation is set to rise, and more
OL,14,Fthan four in five people expect food
OL,15,Fprices to climb."
OL,17,FShe added: "Energy prices are pushing
OL,18,Fup costs for retailers and their
OL,19,Fsupply chains, with the Government's
OL,20,Fenergy taxes and levies making up as
OL,21,Fmuch as 65% of business bills.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOUwD@QO]yD@LOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/5
